cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.IT

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the development of vehicular networks and their communication channel utilization. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also likely as security is an important aspect of vehicular networks. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of VSNs to improve the performance of road traffic control systems. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is relevant as the paper discusses data collection algorithms in a distributed network of vehicles. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of uncertainty estimates to reduce data transmission in a VSN-based road traffic control system, which involves information theory concepts.
